Stream the new Scandinavian Netflix-series The Rain on board your next flight across Europe with our high-speed WiFi. Did you know that The Rain is set in Denmark and Sweden? Read more about The Rain here: https://t.co/gjt2TGFV4c 
#SASHighSpeedWiFi #StreamJustLikeAtHome https://t.co/0tqfP3unxu

Biofuel can reduce CO2 emissions from flying with up to 80 percent. In 2030, SAS aim to utilize an amount of biofuel equaling the consumption from domestic flights.

Learn more: 
https://t.co/kEh7kRp68X https://t.co/ASlWFZAeDU

Breakfast seminar 2: Vad krävs för att alla ska flyga på biobränsle?
https://t.co/UNPFolwO4G

https://t.co/TScl1dorij
Breakfast plans for #Almedalen2018? Meet SAS for inspiring talks on aviation, sustainability and global connectivity. (Links in next tweets) https://t.co/ggwoMeEtk0

Flight routes don't just create jobs in the aviation industry; extensive global connectivity is also a key element in creating general societal and economic growth. Meet SAS at #Almedalen2018 and learn more on the role of aviation and infrastructure: https://t.co/TScl1dorij https://t.co/czUaM7QaGi

Up to the age of 26, you can enjoy special rates by booking a SAS Youth Ticket. Not only will you get a better price, but SAS is the first airline to offer CO2 compensation for all youth tickets. Read more about it here: https://t.co/JfQiKSXx4r https://t.co/0cQ43XyI3R
